name: If you want my tonsils you've got to fight for them!

description:
Check out this special edition that features never before seen images.

The Grays are a cursed family. Dorian Gray IV, the last of his line, struggles with the realization that his personal demons are exactly that… a supernatural force that plagues not only the Grays but many of society’s wealthiest families.

Convinced his redemption is only secured through ridding the city of demons called the Morbi, Dorian launches an ongoing crusade for his soul.

Adaptation of Oscar Wilde's "Dorian Gray".
name: Wilde Ride
The Adventures of Sky Marshal part two

description: 'Hanky-Panky.' Arch and Jug are sweating their upcoming exam and turn to A student Dilton for advice. Surely there's more to acing an exam than just studying hard, right? Discover what Dilton's 'lucky charm' is when it comes to making the grade! Then, 'Welcome to the Digital Age.' Technology sure moves fast. Archie's grandfather marvels at how far computers have come since he was Archie and Chuck's age, giving the teens insight into where computers came from and how they will advance in their lifetime.
name: Hanky Panky

description: 111 pages! Introducing the DADDY of all Digital Exclusives! What better way to celebrate Father's Day than with the proud papas of Archie & the gang? Join Mr. Andrews, Mr. Lodge, Mr. Cooper, and even Lt. Keller for some of Archie Comics' most paternal page-turners! This 100+ page Digital Exclusive pays a special homage to those important men who help us learn to ride a bike, throw a baseball, and--most importantly--supply us with an allowance!

111 pages! As the leaves change colors, Riverdale prepares for autumn. That means school, football, and of course, raking leaves! Will Moose bring the Riverdale Bulldogs to victory? Is Dilton's leaf removal contraption too good to be true? And wait until you see who is crowned as Homecoming Queen! Check out this 111 page Digital Exclusive and FALL for fall!

101 pages! Play ball! Spring has sprung in Riverdale, and for Archie and the gang that can only mean one thing, baseball season! Whether they're coaching a Little League team, watching the pros, or winning the rival game, Archie and his friends always hit it out of the park! With 101 pages celebrating America's pastime, this Digital Exclusive is a home run!

Anyone for tennis? Archie and friends are! Watch the gang make a real "racket" with this 100+ page Digital Exclusive! Riverdale's coolest kids hit the court with some of our best tennis stories by legendary creators like Dan DeCarlo, Samm Schwartz, and Dan Parent! Will Betty or Veronica win Archie's heart with their superior tennis skills? One thing's for sure; when Archie's involved, the score is always 40-LOVE!

113 pages! No tricks here-- this 113 page Digital Exclusive is a real treat! Join Archie and the gang in some spooky fun. From haunted houses to Halloween parties, Riverdale knows how to do the monster mash! What will everyone dress up as this year? Read on to find out! Featuring a special guest appearance by Sabrina the Teenage Witch!

Are you in the mood for some s'mores? Itchin' to take a hike? Feelin' the need to canoe? Well, pack a bag, because it's time to go to camp! Join Archie and his friends for some good ol' fashioned outdoor adventures! Can Archie and the gang survive as camp counselors, or will their campers get the better of them? This Digital Exclusive features over 100 pages of the gang's "campiest" adventures. With Sabrina and Li'l Jinx joining in on the fun, "roughing it" has never been so easy!
115 pages! Enjoy this DIGITAL EXCLUSIVE from Archie!

Just when you thought it was safe to go back in the water... Archie and his chums may be in over their heads in this 100+ page digital exclusive! The gang tangles with some ferocious underwater monsters, including the king of the-- the Great White Shark! Will the gang make it to shore, or will they end up as fish food? Find out in one of our most thrilling Digital Exclusives yet!

Hit the books with Archie, Jughead, and the rest of the gang! The school year is just starting, and so is the drama. But for all the homework, detention, and fashion faux pas, there are also new friends, adventures, and exciting opportunities! Let the students of Riverdale High give you some back-to-school survival tips in this 100+ page Digital Exclusive!

120 pages! "Arrrchie's Buried Treasure" Ahoy, Archie fans! Set sail for adventure in this 120 page Digital Exclusive! Watch as the Riverdale crew dig for treasure, dress as pirates, and daydream about sailing the seven seas. Will Betty & Veronica be able to get rid of a pirate ghost that's fallen in love with them? Will Little Archie escape the clutches of the nefarious Blackbeard? Has Veronica stumbled upon a chest of cursed pirate treasure? Take off that eyepatch and start readin', or you'll walk the plank, matey!

118 pages! Holy Digital Exclusive! Archie, Chuck and the gang are heading to the comic convention! We've collected over 100 pages of the Archie crew's most comical comic con experiences! Which one of the girls will win the Cosplay Costume Contest? Can Chuck Clayton strike a publishing deal for his new comics? And just how will the gang crack the Crooked Comic-Con Caper?! Explore the expanses of the convention floor with creators like Dan Parent, Fernando Ruiz, Alex Segura and Bill Galvan!

98 pages! It's a bird! It's a plane! No, it's a Digital Exclusive! Join Riverdale's teen heroes as they thwart the forces of evil. Can Pureheart battle both The Reptile and Evilheart at once?! Will The Rampaging Rebound bounce all over Captain Hero? And Superteen has her work cut out for her when The Consumer comes along to gobble up Riverdale High! Will our heroes triumph? Tune in to find out!

106 pages! Nothing's more exciting than going to the amusement park- except maybe reading Archie comics! Join the Archie gang as they loop-the-loop, bump some bumper cars, and try their luck at the game corner! This Digital Exclusive collects over 100 pages of amusing amusement park stories. Will Archie survive the dreaded Demon Coaster? Will Reggie get to dunk Jughead at the Dunking Booth? And why is Sabrina trying to ruin the gang's good time? Kick back with some cotton candy and start reading!
119 pages! Put on your earplugs and get ready for another Archie Digital Exclusive!

Strut your stuff with Betty and Veronica! The girls know fashion better than anyone else at Riverdale High, and they're ready to show off. Join the chic crew from Riverdale for a 130 page Digital Exclusive celebration of the latest and greatest fashion trends. And don't miss a special appearance from model extraordinaire Katy Keene!
Betty & Veronica Beat the Heat!

volume.name: Betty and Veronica: Beat the Heat!

description: Get up and move with Betty and Veronica! The girls are experts on staying in shape, and they're ready to share their secrets with you! Join them and the rest of the Riverdale gang as they jog, swim, hit the gym, ride bikes, and even do some rock climbing. Can Betty & Veronica whip the rest of the gang into shape? Who will win the triathalon: Archie or Chuck? And can ANYONE get Jughead off his lazy butt?! Stretch out those laugh muscles and find out!

109 pages! How much food can Jughead eat? That depends on how much food you have! Join Riverdale's favorite bottomless pit in this Digital Exclusive feeding frenzy! We've collected over 100 pages of Jughead's wildest pig-outs, with stories from fan-favorite artists like Rex Lindsey, Fernando Ruiz and Bill Galvan. Can he beat the competition in the pie-eating contest? Can he drop some pounds when his eating habits make him super-sized? And can he stop eating long enough to FALL IN LOVE?! We hope you brought some napkins, folks!

Since her creation in 1962, Sabrina the Teenage Witch has become one of the most popular and endearing characters in American pop culture. To celebrate her 50-year anniversary, Archie Comics presents 50 of Sabrina's most spellbinding stories! This Digital Exclusive collects OVER 350 PAGES of content spanning Sabrina's history, including a NEVER-BEFORE-SEEN origin story, written by Sabrina creator George Gladir himself. So join Sabrina, Salem, Aunties Hilda and Zelda, and many more for the most magical book of the year!

volume.name: Sabrina the Teenage Witch: 50 Magical Stories

description: 109 Pages! It's time to get your game on! Celebrate the legacy of Mobius's speediest hero with a collection of some of his finest video game adaptations! In this second volume, we go back the age of the SEGA Dreamcast! Sonic Adventure reinvigorated the series with whole new game mechanics, many of which exist to this day. This Digital Exclusive includes over 110 pages of Sonic's next-gen adventures and features adaptations of Sonic Adventure, Sonic Shuffle, and Sonic Adventure 2!

101 pages! It's time to get your game on! Celebrate the legacy of Mobius's speediest hero with a collection of some of his finest video game adaptations! This third volume focuses on Sonic's most recent adventures, from alternate dimensions to interstellar amusement parks. Read comic adaptations of Sonic Rush, Sonic Unleashed, Sonic Generations and more. Plus, check out a never-before-seen cover gallery to see how the Sonic comics have been inspired by the games over the years!

name: No. 47, 2012

description: Archie and Betty struggle with their careers in the fast-paced environment of the 'Big Apple.' But when a mysterious figure from their past offers Archie eternal wealth in exchange for leaving Betty and returning to Riverdale, will the temptation of an end to their struggles prove too much?
In 'Archie Loves Betty: Different Drummers,' Archie and Betty face challenges in their careers, but a little help from friends could reignite the dreams that brought them to the Big Apple.
Archie and Betty fight to make their dreams come true in Manhattan. But back in Riverdale, Mr. Lodge will stop at nothing to break the man that broke his daughter's heart.
Mr. Lodge's plot to destroy Archie has just begun. Who will the couple turn to when Betty is fired and Ambrose's Chowder House is in serious danger?
The newlyweds return home for a triple wedding as every break for Archie and Betty crumbles. Is someone manipulating their fates? Who, and why?
Archie and friends must now confront the most shocking development of all, as a beloved friend passes away! But even this dark cloud has a silver lining.
Archie and Betty come home to Riverdale to start their careers in education, but Mr. Lodge is out to shut down their beloved Riverdale High!
Archie and Betty prep for life as teachers, but Mr. Lodge has other plans. The consequences are costly when Veronica and Reggie get too close to his scheme.

The married life continues in 'Archie Loves Betty: Freshman Year: First Semester.' Archie and Betty struggle as new teachers to connect with their rowdy and sometimes outrageous students. In 'Archie Loves Veronica: The Trial of Reggie Mantle,' Archie and Veronica take Lodge Industries to new heights! But it's not part of Mr. Lodge's plan. Can the two survive his cunning this time?

In 'Archie Loves Betty: Freshman Year-The First Semester' Part 4, Archie makes a startling realization about his career, while Betty discovers a new mission. Meanwhile, in 'Archie Loves Veronica: The Trial of Reggie Mantle' Part 4' Reggie stands trial! But for what?

Special Summer Swimsuit issue! In 'Archie Loves Veronica,' Ronnie makes a surprise discovery that could affect her finances with Archie. Plus, where's Jughead? In 'Archie Loves Betty,' Archie takes a more hard-line approach to his students, but will it work? How will Veronica and Jason Blossom's relationship, well, blossom?
In this issue of 'Archie Marries Betty', being teachers is beginning to take its toll on the couple and Veronica finds out something unpleasant about the man she's interested in.

In 'Archie Loves Betty,' Archie finds comfort in teaching and scouting musical talent for Ambrose's club, the Chowhouse. All the while, Hiram Lodge's world turns dark when Veronica's plane goes missing and Fred Mirth continues his scheme to take over Lodge Industries.

The madcap adventure continues in 'Archie Loves Betty' as Archie's universe is turned upside down upon catching sight of Mr. Lodge conducting a secret rendezvous with Mr. Lodge? And who is the masked stranger who seems to be guiding this evening's events?

What do Archie's day dreams have to do with Veronica's mysterious disappearance? And how will Dilton's multiverse theory come into play? Another piece of the puzzle falls into place and you won't want to miss it!

In 'Archie Marries Betty' Kevin's wedding is upon us and you're on the guest list! But how exactly did Kevin meet his significant other? Meanwhile, Archie juggles teaching responsibilities with his marriage to Betty. Don't miss out on the wedding event of the year that everyone's talking about!

'Archie Marries Betty.' Archie must work out his priorities between his nightclub venture and responsibilities to his students. Meanwhile Midge has big news for Jughead and Reggie's investigation into Veronica's missing plane catches the attention of the FBI.

In the alternate reality, Archie digs deeper into the mysteries surrounding Dilton, Fred Mirth, and Memory Lane! Plus what exactly did happen with Veronica's missing plane? Things are about to come to a head as this issue blows open the lid on every crazy event that lead us to this point! You are not going to want to miss the thrilling conclusion!

'Archie Marries Betty: Rock On!' Part 1. It's an all-around homecoming with several familiar faces making their way back to Riverdale! Archie and Ambrose make plans to jump-start their joint business venture plus Archie hears the words he never thought possible from the lips of Mr. Lodge!

Archie's students celebrate their battle of the bands victory! Betty uses her warm disposition to help a student in need while Jughead's kid sister Jellybean pitches in at the Chok'lit Shoppe, but there's something she's not telling him!

Archie Marries Betty: Cheryl makes her return to Riverdale after a stint of chasing her dreams in Hollywood but it's not the happiest of homecomings as she has bigger issues than trying to get her acting career off the ground. Don't miss this game changing issue of the most critically acclaimed Archie title ever!

The gang welcomes back an old friend in need of support during a trying time. Cheryl Blossom breaks the news of her cancer diagnoses in the most touching issue of Life with Archie yet, proving that in Riverdale, home is truly where the heart is!

Archie and his business partners have just booked the biggest band in the world for their club's opening night! All that's left is to schedule the opening act -- is an Archies reunion in the cards? Cheryl continues to fight the good fight with her chemo treatments and having a friend like Veronica along makes it all the more bearable. Don't miss this touching issue that proves no matter how rough life gets in Riverdale, the gang is ready to take on anything life throws at them -- together.

Archie faces pressure from his boss and Veronica's father, Mr. Lodge. Forced to buy out Pop Tate's Chok'lit Shoppe for Lodge Industries, Archie instigates a near-violent dispute. Can Archie, Veronica and their friends find happiness as they face the challenge of saving Pop's future as well as their own?
Lodge Industries' plan to buy out Pop Tate's is tearing Archie and Veronica apart. Can the once resilient teens survive the woes brought on by political tricks, money troubles and love gone awry?
The Lodge's push to buy out Pop Tate's is pushing Archie and Veronica's marriage to its limits as the mayoral race continues. Will an old foe step in to help Moose step up?
Archie and Veronica fight to fix their marriage miles apart. Veronica must choose between trusting her husband or her father.
Political sniping and corporate greed rear their ugly heads, with the town, Moose's mayoral aspirations, and Archie and Veronica's marriage all at stake!
Veronica stands up against her industrialist dad to save Riverdale, as Moose's mayoral campaign rolls on!
Newly appointed mayor Moose Mason has his hands full when Reggie is framed for the exposed corporate corruption that lead to his mayoral victory!
Framed by Mr. Lodge, Reggie Mantle awaits his trial. Fueled by their new romance, can Betty rescue him before he takes the fall?
Archie and Veronica take Lodge Industries to new heights! But it's not part of Mr. Lodge's plan. Can the two survive his cunning this time?

Now With 80 Pages And More New Stories! In 'Archie Loves Betty: Freshman Year-The First Semester' Part 4, Archie makes a startling realization about his career, while Betty discovers a new mission. Meanwhile, in 'Archie Loves Veronica: The Trial of Reggie Mantle' Part 4' Reggie stands trial!

Special Summer Swimsuit issue! In 'Archie Loves Veronica,' Ronnie makes a surprise discovery that could affect her finances with Archie. Plus, where's Jughead? In 'Archie Loves Betty,' Archie takes a more hard-line approach to his students, but will it work? How will Veronica and Jason Blossom's relationship, well, blossom?
